{{Lunisolar March}}
'''March 27''' is the 27th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安}}.

== Events ==
* ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1392]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日}}) – {{ill|Yi Seong-gye|ja|李成桂}} founded the 【Yi Dynasty (Joseon)†Joseon】.
* {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1671]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日}}) – The internal conflict within the 【Sendai Domain†Sendai_Domain】, known as the {{ill|Date-sōdō|ja|伊達騒動}}, was resolved by the bakufu.
* {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1689]] {{ill|May 16|ja|5月16日}}) – {{ill|Matsuo Bashō|ja|松尾芭蕉}} departed on his journey to compose 【Oku no Hosomichi|ja:奥の細道】 together with his disciple {{ill|Kawai Sōra|ja|河合曾良}}.
* {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1854]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日}}) – {{ill|Yoshida Shōin|ja|吉田松陰}} sought passage on an American black ship anchored at Shimoda but was refused.
* {{ill|Genji|ja|元治}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1864]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日}}) – The Tengu-dō Rebellion occurred, when the Sonnō jōi faction of the Mito Domain, led by {{ill|Fujita Koshirō|ja|藤田小四郎}}, rose in arms at Mount Tsukuba.

