'''March 27''' is the 27th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|qid=Q96759844|1=taian}}{{efn|ja|大安|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|1=taian|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1306255}}.

== Events ==
* ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1392|en|1392|qid=Q6382|lt=1392|1=1392}} {{ill|April 19|en|April 19|qid=Q2523|lt=April 19|1=April 19}}) – {{ill|Taejo of Joseon|en|Taejo of Joseon|qid=Q378483|lt=Yi Seong-gye|1=Taejo of Joseon}} founded the 【Yi Dynasty (Joseon)†Joseon】.
* {{ill|Kanbun (era)|en|Kanbun (era)|qid=Q1146228|lt=Kanbun|1=Kanbun (era)}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1671|en|1671|qid=Q7610|lt=1671|1=1671}} {{ill|May 6|en|May 6|qid=Q2552|lt=May 6|1=May 6}}) – The internal conflict within the 【Sendai Domain†Sendai_Domain】, known as the {{ill|Date Sōdō|en|Date Sōdō|qid=Q1172302|lt=Date-sōdō|1=Date Sōdō}}, was resolved by the bakufu.
* {{ill|Genroku|en|Genroku|qid=Q1325001|lt=Genroku|1=Genroku}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1689|en|1689|qid=Q7674|lt=1689|1=1689}} {{ill|May 16|en|May 16|qid=Q2574|lt=May 16|1=May 16}}) – {{ill|Matsuo Bashō|en|Matsuo Bashō|qid=Q5676|lt=Matsuo Bashō|1=Matsuo Bashō}} departed on his journey to compose 【Oku no Hosomichi|ja:奥の細道】 together with his disciple {{ill|Kawai Sōra|ja|河合曾良|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawai Sōra|1=Kawai Sora|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11141924}}.
* {{ill|Ansei|en|Ansei|qid=Q1327259|lt=Ansei|1=Ansei}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1854|en|1854|qid=Q7670|lt=1854|1=1854}} {{ill|April 24|en|April 24|qid=Q2529|lt=April 24|1=April 24}}) – {{ill|Yoshida Shōin|en|Yoshida Shōin|qid=Q559747|lt=Yoshida Shōin|1=Yoshida Shōin}} sought passage on an American black ship anchored at Shimoda but was refused.
* {{ill|Genji era|en|Genji era|qid=Q1325419|lt=Genji|1=Genji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1864|en|1864|qid=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}} {{ill|May 2|en|May 2|qid=Q2545|lt=May 2|1=May 2}}) – The Tengu-dō Rebellion occurred, when the Sonnō jōi faction of the Mito Domain, led by {{ill|Fujita Koshirō|ja|藤田小四郎|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujita Koshirō|1=Fujita Kishirō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11288247}}, rose in arms at Mount Tsukuba.

